==English==
===Etymology===
*[[poly-]] + [[diamond|(d)iamond]], the polyiamond made up of two triangles being a diamond or [[rhombus]]

===Noun===
'''polyiamond''' (''plural'' '''polyiamonds''')
{{wikipedia}}
#{{geometry}} A [[polyform]] made by joining one or more [[equilateral triangle]]s edge to edge in various [[arrangement]]s.

